In a little while, ladies and gentlemen, we are going to give our opinion on the appointment of two members of the Court of Auditors.
I have in front of me the French versions of those reports: one of them has been drawn up by Mr PomÃ©s Ruiz, a Spanish rapporteur, on the Bulgarian candidate; the other, by a Hungarian rapporteur, on a Romanian candidate!
In these French versions, the biographies of the members of the Court of Auditors and the questionnaires are in English. So there we have an important area for Mr Orban to work on: ensuring that linguistic diversity is respected in our institutions!
